originalText.text: It was extremely easy to notice the low ethical and intellectual standards of its staff the moment I entered the parking lot. The employees were full of agressive energy and could not understand basic concepts of math or driving. Message to the owner of GMC Parking: you really need to get higher quality people working there.

originalText.text: NO STARS. Damage and theft.  After being a patron for many years, they cancelled my contract because I kept inquiring about damage to my car. They are habitually late in getting your car ready.  They will ding and scratch you car.  They will steal things from your car.  And then they will lie about it.  This garage is not run by Columbia.  The management of this garage will not believe you if you report abuse or bad service.  Terrible, unethical, liars.

originalText.text: Absolutely terrible communication. We got to the garage at 7:45am and they gave us an “early-bird” 12-hr parking special. We were told we could park from 8am-8pm and pay a fee of $21. We came at 6:11pm and were charged $54 for the full price because apparently the “early-bird” parking ended at 6pm. 1. We were not told that and 2. Were eleven minutes late and had to pay $33 more for 11 minutes. Definitely will not be parking here again, would not recommend; I would rate 0 stars if I could.

originalText.text:
Decent Garage, Pricy as all hell but reasonable for the area. The guys working there are mostly pretty ok, and nobody raised a fuss when I brought my car in totally dea. Told them my mechanic couldn't take delivery til next morning we just shoved it into the corner. It's an old building and whatever the roof is made of comes off sometimes so you get plaster dust on your car sometimes, but I've never once been in an NYC garage that didn't have this problem.

Definitely backs up like crazy around 7-10am but otherwise you can just pull in, leave your keys on the seat and be gone.

They also have an awful bathroom that you can use. Probably not so nice for ladies but as a guy it's nice if you've been stuck in traffic on the sawmill for hours.

Also I've left nice stuff in my car there in plain view plenty of times for years and never had anything jacked, so not really sure what the reviews complaining about theft are about.

originalText.text: Attendant was rude and possibly inebriated. I walked back after 10 min to ask for a refund because I had an uneasy feeling, given the items stoted in my car, and was not given a refund.
